.TH GITY "1" "June 2026" "gity  Gity Version -> 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
gity \- manual page for gity  Gity Version -> 1.0
.SH DESCRIPTION
usage: gity [\-h] [\-f] [\-p] [\-l] [\-a] [\-s SAVE_PATH] [\-d DELETE_PATH]
.IP
[\-g GET_PATH] [\-j] [\-\-search\-paths]
[\-\-set\-max\-depth SET_MAX_DEPTH]
[\-\-include\-submodules INCLUDE_SUBMODULES] [\-\-view\-config] [\-v]
.PP
Run git\-status on all local repositories at once. Without arguments, Gity will
search directories specified in 'gity \fB\-\-show\-default\fR' up to 3 levels and
execute git status on them.
.SS "options:"
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
show this help message and exit
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-fetch\fR
Execute git fetch on all repos found by Gity.
.TP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-pull\fR
Execute git pull on all repos found by Gity.
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-list\fR
List all repositories Gity found in the current home
directory.
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Recursivly search entire home directory rather than
default directories.
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-save\-path\fR SAVE_PATH
Save a new directory to the default search paths.
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-delete\-path\fR DELETE_PATH
Save a new directory to the default search paths.
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-get\-path\fR GET_PATH
Prints the path for a specified repository name. (used
for jump)
.TP
\fB\-j\fR, \fB\-\-jump\-setup\fR
Create alias to use the jump shortcut feature.
.TP
\fB\-\-search\-paths\fR
Show search paths Gity will use when no arguments are
given.
.TP
\fB\-\-set\-max\-depth\fR SET_MAX_DEPTH
Set the max # recursion levels to search.(INT)(default
is 3)(recursion depth)
.TP
\fB\-\-include\-submodules\fR INCLUDE_SUBMODULES
Set config to include/exclude submodules in Gity
output.(TRUE/FALSE)(Default is false)(only recognizes
modern submodules that use '.git' files)
.TP
\fB\-\-view\-config\fR
Print Gity config and exit.
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version info and exit.
.IP
